Help create a Better Weekday

  Lookers

They've just started their journey and have only saved a profile or viewed a job.

  Engagers

These job seekers have uploaded a resume, engaged with jobs, and possibly ready to apply.

  All-Stars

This group has done all the above, completed recommended tasks, and shown interest in many jobs.

Customer Success Job Posted!

To view stats on this posting without an account, use this unique url: http://app.betterweekdays.com/job/12345?key=aldskflaiwepr13upoinewofipneopwanifa

Posted 10/1/2015

careerservices@university.edu

Business Administration, Marketing, Accounting
Views
22

8
Company
ABC, Inc.
URL
abccompany.com
Location
St. Louis
Position Title
Customer Success
Contact Email
hiring@abccompany.com
Contact URL
abccompany.com/myjob/apply

Description and Responsibilities

As a Success Champion, you’ll help on-board customers, respond to inbound requests, craft informative messages, and build vital relationships.

You are an empathetic communicator who will help our customers learn. You are also interested in analyzing trends and creatively coming up with processes to optimize processes. We’re growing fast and you don’t need to be micromanaged. You thrive with in clear customer success goals and you do exceptional work.
Responsibilities:
• Propose ways to iterate on the customer success program strategy through trials and data analysis
• Provide one-to-one and group coaching to increase product engagement and retention
• Understand all of Better Weekday's feature set and mission
• Support our customers and prospective customers via on-site on-boarding, phone, email, live chat, and webinars
• Identify, propose, and initiate projects that can help our customers be more successful
Required Skills/Experience:
• Outstanding verbal and written communication skills
• Passion for technology
• Interest in design thinking
• Empathetic and patient
• Proactive leadership skills
• Desire to work in an ever-changing, experimental environment
• Demonstrated ability to give and receive feedback and adapt quickly

Marketing Manager

Company

Hallmark Cards

  • Formed: 1910
  • Annual Revenues: $3.8 billion
  • Employees: 3,453
  • Website
  • Wikipedia
  • Google Plus

Location

Kansas City, MO

  • Population: 820,445
  • Avg. Monthly Cost: 2.5k
  • Humid Continental Climate
  • Events
  • Points of Interest
  • Neighborhoods

Schedule

40hr Week

  • 8 hr days
  • 5 days per week
  • 3 weeks time off
  • Vacation Policy
  • Sick / Personal Day Policy

Compensation

$29,600 Annual

  • $2,466 Monthly
  • $15.40 Hourly
  • You
  • The Job
  • What It's Like

This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.

Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:

  • Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patients discharge appointments.
  • Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.
  • Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.
  • Maintaining office supplies.
  • Providing professional and courteous customer service.
  • Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.
  • Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.
  • Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.
  • Interpreting and transcribing doctors orders.
  • Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control

This is where the job description goes, if it exists.

People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

                                                            <p>This position is located in PCS/Clinical Support Service. Incumbent in this roles will be responsible for performing a variety of administrative and clerical duties and is the liaison between the nursing staff in their assigned area and customers both internal and external to the medical center.</p>
                                                            <p>Specialized experience includes, but is not limited, to the following:</p>
                                                            <ul>
                                                            <li>Scheduling, canceling and rescheduling patients discharge appointments.</li>
                                                            <li>Accurately and timely processing patient information, admits, discharge, appointments and transfers in computer system.</li>
                                                            <li>Arranging and coordinating in-patient procedure appointments for timeliness.</li>
                                                            <li>Maintaining office supplies.</li>
                                                            <li>Providing professional and courteous customer service.</li>
                                                            <li>Assisting with the orientation/on the job training of new staff.</li>
                                                            <li>Completing work orders and contacting appropriate staff when requested for emergency repairs or special requests.</li>
                                                            <li>Inputting and extracting data of a highly technical nature.</li>
                                                            <li>Interpreting and transcribing doctors orders.</li>
                                                            <li>Maintaining patient records, scanning, quality control</li>
                                                            </ul>                                                        </div>

Marketing Associate

Hallmark Cards

Kansas City, MO

Work / Life Balance

★★★½

Job Outlook

★★★★½

Culture & Values

Compensation

$29,960 median salary

They're looking for: Attention to Detail, Dependability, Cooperation, Integrity

I'll be responsible for: Record patients' medical history, vital statistics, or information such as test results in medical records.

I'll also be responsible for: Prepare treatment rooms for patient examinations, keeping the rooms neat and clean.

People who work here say: The people. Everyone here works as hard as they can toward a shared mission.

They also say: Leadership is not taught or valued here - and it's needed. Managers are not empowered to make decisions for their departments, and they are not listened to.

Helpful Articles

Why NOW Is The Time To Invest In Career Services

The rising cost of higher education has many concerned, especially when it comes to the return on investment. As a result, institutions must make more strategic investments in their programs and services to demonstrate their value to their customers—students.

Source: Better Weekdays

How to make your Career Center a Netflix, NOT a Blockbuster

We all know the sad story of Blockbuster – Once the king of home entertainment, it spiraled into a tunnel of no return, and now it’s nothing but a memory to most.

Source: Better Weekdays

How to Help Frustrated Graduates: A Career Counselor’s Guide

As a new graduate, it’s nerve-wracking to find a job. If countless cover letters turn into zero interviews, recent alumni can feel angry at their university, financially-frustrated, and generally disappointed.

Source: Better Weekdays

Frequently Asked Questions

Helpful Student Engagement Tips

What's the best way to follow-up with employers once connected?

Follow up with thank-you notes to employers, preferably a hand written letter or postcard rather than an email.

What is the most important step when establishing employer relationships?

When approaching a potential partner, be sure to explain how the employer will benefit such as making valuable new connections, promoting their brand, and gaining access to potential employees.

© 2015 Better Weekdays. All rights reserved.

New To-Do Rule

Active Rules

Title Actions

When Monsanto views a student profile, send me an email Edit | Delete
When any student views the Marketing Associate position, create a to-do with title "reach out to them" Edit | Delete
